<font color="#FF0000">ARE WE LOSING OUR HOME SITE?</font><br>
<tt>Thu Apr 10 12:52:55 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
When I heard the news, bad, and saw the drop off in  postings, and also saw the decline in my e mail, which I welcome without reservations from all of you, I got worried. <br><br>
I began to search the WWW for something that might be of help, might be similiar, might be &quot;our&quot; new home.  I am concerned because I get about 4 or 5 e mails for every post, and while I am not a Dear Abby or a cyberspace Dr. Freud, I know, because I have felt the pain, that many of you out there don't want to post, but do want to &quot;reach out and touch some one&quot;.  Pardon the phrase.<br><br>
In that theme, I contacted Kali Tal and her 60's homepage/vietnam generation place. What a mistake I made. A mistake that was giant, but innocent in intent.  This is one bad and meanspirited lady, at best, and I don't want to dignify whatever she is at worst.<br><br>
In less than polite terms, she let me know that she knew of this site, but her's was more correct, and better, and her opinion of the site was: &quot;it's a<br>
&gt;place where the same tired sentiments about the war are<br>
&gt;rehashed, without<br>
&gt;critical appraisal, over and over again, without providing<br>
&gt;new insight or<br>
&gt;new perspectives.<br><br>
Wow, said I, this is one strong woman, however misguided.<br><br>
But then she went on to state that she was quite &quot;picky&quot; about who she &quot;allowed&quot; on her site, because she is the &quot;editor&quot; and god,knows, the editor is supreme.  After she got done putting down the PBS POV site, and praising her site, and her ability, she than launched a politically correct attack at Moi!  At that point I lost it and retaliated.<br><br>
So much is history, even if rewritten.  She now is upset at me for sharing her opinion with some of you.  That opinion is that as an editor, she is entitled to act like Joe Stalin, and govern a generation and a war, both of which she was not part of.  The irony and the oxymoron of that I will<br>
decline to comment on.<br><br>
I may have been wrong to share her hate, I mean e mail, with a few, but God, I have never heard such narcissistic hate since I did civil rights work in the late 50&quot;s.  ENOUGH SAID ABOUT HER.  Go check her out if you must, I will erase the wasted memories and energies I spent in that vain.  I wish POV the best, and I hope we all will continue on here with healing, learning, and the positive values that make life worth living, not the vain ego-istic ramblings of clearly, an academic &quot;professional&quot; gone amiss.
<p><code>-- shrink4u@irvine.quik.com  (doc Spatz) </code><p>


